CONTEXT KleeneCombinedOperators IN ENGLISH

PURPOSE CONTEXT KleeneCombinedOperators MARKDOWN
{+ Kleene operators applied to COMPOUND terms and stacked on each other.
   Base: r = {(x,y)}, q = {(y,z)}, so r \/ q is the chain x -> y -> z.

   Stressed here:
   * closure of a union term: (r \/ q)+ pinned exactly;
   * reduction of a compound term: (r \/ q)% = r \/ q (a chain is reduced);
   * converse commutes with closure and with reduction - the reduction case
     is lemma red_converse in proofs/kleene/KleeneReduction.thy;
   * stacked closures: (s*)* = s*, (s+)* = s*, (s*)+ = s* - nested
     WITH RECURSIVE evaluation in SQL.
+}

RELATION r[Node*Node]
POPULATION r CONTAINS [ ("x","y") ]

RELATION q[Node*Node]
POPULATION q CONTAINS [ ("y","z") ]

RELATION expectedPlus[Node*Node]
MEANING "The closure of the union of r and q on the chain x -> y -> z."
POPULATION expectedPlus CONTAINS
  [ ("x","y"), ("y","z"), ("x","z") ]

RULE unionPlusExact      : (r \/ q)+ = expectedPlus
RULE unionRedIsBase      : (r \/ q)% = r \/ q
RULE converseAfterPlus   : ((r \/ q)~)+ = ((r \/ q)+)~
RULE converseAfterRed    : ((r \/ q)~)% = ((r \/ q)%)~
RULE starIdempotent      : ((r \/ q)*)* = (r \/ q)*
RULE plusOfStar          : ((r \/ q)*)+ = (r \/ q)*
RULE starOfPlus          : ((r \/ q)+)* = (r \/ q)*

INTERFACE Combined : "_SESSION"[SESSION] ; V[SESSION*Node]
   CRud BOX<TABLE sortable>
   [ "node"      : I[Node]      cRud
   , "unionPlus" : (r \/ q)+    cRud
   , "unionStar" : (r \/ q)*    cRud
   , "unionRed"  : (r \/ q)%    cRud
   ]

ENDCONTEXT
